CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 11, 1958, pg. A1 reads: "70-Gal. 'Moonshine' Raid - Lieut. Stanley Maskell of Centre Ave. Police Station looks over 70 gallons of evidence brought into the station by Lieut. James Devitt and Patrolmen Ogelsby and Cherevka (not shown) following a moonshine raid by the latter three officers at 529 Roberts St. John Jones, 36, of that address, was arrested for violation of state liquor laws and held for court by Magistrate Robert (Pappy) Williams. - Harris Photo."Stanley Maskell (1907-1998) joined the Pittsburgh police in 1937, and was made Lieutenant in 1946.  He retired in 1964.
TitMainTitle: Police Lieutenant Stanley Maskell kneeling among gallons of moonshine after raid at home of John Jones at 529 Roberts Street, in Centre Avenue Police Station, Hill District, another version
